x4freetext: PHOTONEUTRON ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS FOR HE-4.

x4codes.hlp: Univ. of Toronto, Toronto, Ontario, Canada

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Canadian Journal of Physics, Vol.53, p.802 (1975)

x4codes.hlp: Univ. of Toronto, Toronto, Ontario, Canada

x4freetext: .THE ELECTRON BEAM CHARACTERISTICS:PEAK
CURRENT=0.4 A, PULSE WIDTH=15 NS, REPETITION  RATE=360
HZ.
. THE BREMSSTRAHLUNG TARGET CONSISTED OF 0.20 CM
THICK TUNGSTEN PLATE BACKED BY A 4.45 CM THICK ALUMIN-
IUM ELECTRON BEAM STOP.
THE LIQUID HELIUM SAMPLE DEWAR. THE IRRADIATED PART OF
THE SAMPLE DEWAR WAS 5.08 CM IN DIAMETER AND WAS CONS-
TRUCTED OF 0.25 MM ALUMINIUM WALLS.
.FLIGHT PATH=49.5 M.
.THE NEUTRON DETECTOR CONSISTS OF AN OXYGEN POI-
SONED LIQUID SCINTILLATOR (12.7 CM THICK BY 35.6 CM IN
DIAMETER,NE 213) VIEWED BY THREE PHILIPS XP1040 PHOTO-
MULTIPLIER TUBES.
THE BREMSSTRAHLUNG SHAPE WAS OBTAINED FROM MEASUREMEN-
TS  OF PHOTONEUTRON SPECTRA  FROM  0.64 CM THICK HEAVY
WATER (D2O) AND WATER (H2O)  SLAB TARGETS CONTAINED IN
HOLDERS WITH 0.01 CM THICK MYLAR WALLS. TO  OBTAIN THE
CROSS SECTIONS THE PHOTONEUTRON SPECTRA HAD BEEN ALIG-
NED TO COMMON CENTER OF MASS ENERGY BINS AND NORMALIZ-
ED TO THE SAME BREMSSTRAHLUNG DOSE. THE CROSS SECTIONS
WERE OBTAINED BY DIVIDING THE SPECTRA BY THE APPROPRI-
ATE BREMSSTRAHLUNG DISTRIBUTIONS.THE TOTAL CROSS SECT-
ION WAS OBTAINED BY NORMALIZING ON CROSS SECTION MEAS-
URED BY IRISH ET AL.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: .THE STATISTICAL UNCERTAINTIES ARE REPORTED.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.8, p.1211 (1973)

x4freetext: THE DATA WERE  CORRECTED FOR (A) THE NEUTRONS PRODUCED
IN THE ALUMINIUM;(B) THE NEUTRONS SCATTERED BY THE HE-
LIUM SAMPLE; (C) THE THICK SAMPLE.
THE DOUBLE DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTION FOR THE REACTION
HE-4(G,N)HE-3  HAS BEEN MEASURED  AT LABORATORY ANGLES
OF 53,68,83,98,128 AND 143 DEGREES FOR EXCITATION ENE-
RGIES BETWEEN 22 AND 32 MEV BY  THE PHOTONEUTRON  TIME
OF FLIGHT TECHNIQUE.THE PHOTONEUTRON SPECTRA WERE USED
TO OBTAIN THE ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION COEFFICIENTS IN THE
LEGENDRE SERIES EXPANSION FOR THE DIFFERENTIAL  PHOTO-
NEUTRON CROSS SECTIONS. ANALYSIS OF THESE COEFFICIENTS
INDICATES THAT THE PHOTODISINTEGRATION PROCESS IN THIS
NUCLEUS, WHILE DOMINATED BY E1 PHOTON ABSORPTION FOLL-
OWED BY CHANNEL SPIN ZERO(NO SPIN FLIP) P-WAVE NEUTRON
EMISSION,IS AFFECTED BY E1 CHANNEL SPIN ONE AND E2 CO-
NTRIBUTIONS.IN THE HIGHER ENERGY REGION (E>27 MEV) THE
AMOUNT OF E2 ABSORPTION OBSERVED WAS 6 PER CENT OF THE
TOTAL AND IS DOMINATED BY THE CHANNEL SPIN ONE E2 MAT-
RIX ELEMENT.
